public class IndexedNameMap<T extends com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.Named> extends BaseIndexedMap<String,T>
Stores named values by name and also makes them accessible by index in the order in which the valAues were added, where 0 is the first value and n-1 is the last value in a map with n entries.

Example

  class Fruit implements Named
 class Apple extends Fruit
 class Banana extends Fruit

 var map = new IndexedNameMap<Fruit>();
 map.add(new Apple());
 map.add(new Banana());

 map.get(0);        // Apple
 map.get("Apple");  // Apple
